The paper proposes a new approach to domain adaptation in deep networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision. The paper specifically focuses on deep neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed method involves feature adaptation, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of residual layers, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the use of loss functions and back-propagation, which are fundamental concepts in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
